quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his courtiers, so he said: “I am a messenger of the Lord of the worlds.”"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"Every sign We showed them was greater than the one before it, and We seized them with punishment so that they may turn in repentance"
  43,49,"They said, “O magician, call upon your Lord for us, by virtue of the covenant He has made with you; we will surely accept guidance.”"
  43,50,"But as soon We removed the punishment from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"Pharaoh proclaimed to his people, “O my people, does not the kingdom of Egypt belong to me, and these streams flowing at my feet? Do you not see"
  43,52,Or am I not better than this contemptible one who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Then why there are not sent down upon him bracelets of gold or come with him angels to support him?”
  43,54,Thus he made fool of his people and they obeyed him. They were indeed a wicked people
  43,55,"When they angered Us, We exacted Our retribution and drowned them all"
  43,56,Thus We made them a precedent and an example for the later generations